title: The Crystal Stopper
creator: Maurice LeBlanc
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of The Crystal Stopper by Maurice LeBlanc. Read by Cathy Barratt During a burglary at the home of Deputy Daubrecq a crime is committed, and two accomplices of Arsène Lupin are arrested by the police. One is guilty of the crime, the other innocent, but both will be sentenced to death. Lupin seeks to deliver the victim of a miscarriage of justice, but struggles against Deputy Daubrecq's ruthless blackmailer, who has an incriminating document hidden in a crystal stopper. (Summary by Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; audiobooks; mystery; Arsène Lupin, gentleman thief; murder

reviews.reviewbody:
A document is needed to save the life of a beloved co-conspirator who is doomed to the gallows, and Arsine Lupin is determined to find it, but the criminal in the case seems to be a step ahead of him all the time!  The criminal is also allied with the police force who are more interested in stopping Lupin than stopping him.  Can Lupin find the document before it is too late?

Excellent story, excellent reading.  Enjoy!
